{"gems":{"name":"getargv","downloads":6444,"version":"0.3.15","version_created_at":"2026-03-20T19:17:04.242Z","version_downloads":18,"platform":"universal-darwin","authors":"Camden Narzt","info":"== Getargv\nGetargv is a gem that allows you to query the arguments of other processes as an array or string.\n\nThis gem only supports macOS because the +KERN_PROCARGS2+ sysctl only exists in xnu kernels, BSD or Linux users should just read <code>/proc/$PID/cmdline</code> which is much easier and faster, Solaris users should use pargs.\n\nThis gem requires you have {libgetargv}[https://getargv.narzt.cam/] installed.\n\nTo limit the getargv gem to Apple OSs add it to your Gemfile like so:\n\n  gem \"getargv\", \"~> 0.3.15\", platforms: :ruby, install_if: RbConfig::CONFIG[\"host_os\"].include?(\"darwin\")\n","licenses":["BSD-3-Clause"],"metadata":{"funding_uri":"https://github.com/sponsors/CamJN","homepage_uri":"https://getargv.narzt.cam/","changelog_uri":"https://github.com/getargv/getargv.rb/blob/CHANGELOG.md","bug_tracker_uri":"https://github.com/getargv/getargv.rb/issues","source_code_uri":"https://github.com/getargv/getargv.rb","documentation_uri":"https://rubydoc.info/gems/getargv/Getargv"},"yanked":false,"sha":"53f4ca97cf20bbce569bbe094f67fd4a125dfd05636bd07cc624700d02d25a10","spec_sha":"26e0a046a19e07cf1c89cc76f8ced8b8482c1f387997631fbfa64284e11761aa","project_uri":"https://rubygems.org/gems/getargv","gem_uri":"https://rubygems.org/gems/getargv-0.3.15-universal-darwin.gem","homepage_uri":"https://getargv.narzt.cam/","wiki_uri":null,"documentation_uri":"https://rubydoc.info/gems/getargv/Getargv","mailing_list_uri":null,"source_code_uri":"https://github.com/getargv/getargv.rb","bug_tracker_uri":"https://github.com/getargv/getargv.rb/issues","changelog_uri":"https://github.com/getargv/getargv.rb/blob/CHANGELOG.md","funding_uri":"https://github.com/sponsors/CamJN","dependencies":{"development":[{"name":"bump","requirements":">= 0"},{"name":"minitest","requirements":">= 0